    {
      "body": "The train was powered by fire, which emitted smoke that billowed through two pipes on top of the engine, while two headlights on the lower front of the engine provided illumination when needed. The interior of the locomotive had many pipes, levers, and meters, all of which were metallic, while the passenger cars themselves were mostly wooden and had several windows with two panes of glass divided by a wooden bar and bordered by a red curtain.",
